	                     Reset image size
					</button></span></div></div><figcaption><div class="article-text figure-caption"><p><strong>Figure 3.</strong> Asymmetric reciprocal-space maps of diffracted intensity measured from two Bi<sub><em>m</em></sub>Te<sub><em>n</em></sub> films deposited on BaF<sub>2</sub> (1 1 1) substrates at high (left) and low (right) excess Te flux. '<em>S</em>' marks the 313 diffraction maximum of the substrate, '<em>L</em>' denote the 10–1.20<sup>(23)</sup> diffraction peak of Bi<sub>2</sub>Te<sub>3</sub> and 10–1.16<sup>(11)</sup> diffraction peak of Bi<sub>1</sub>Te<sub>1</sub>.</p></div><p class="mb-05 print-hide">Download figure:</p><span class="btn-multi-block print-hide"><a class="btn btn-primary fig-dwnld-std-img" id="wd-jnl-art-btn-std-img-ansnaa5953f03" href="/2043-6262/8/1/015006/downloadFigure/figure/ansnaa5953f03"><span class="icon-image"></span>
